<subSubSection id="0F92373FBB12F496EC413AB188091822" pageId="0" pageNumber="21" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="16CA111DDC0A08C1EF1046FD5F645603" pageId="0" pageNumber="21">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="72B8449738574A2AD784B50417EE9A65" pageId="0" pageNumber="21">
Differs from 
<taxonomicName id="8CB3821FD59E52A02F2B6F1FB184FF7F" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Clavicipitaceae" genus="Trochila" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Trochila ilicina" order="Helotiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="21" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="ilicina">
<emphasis id="6716C8BE0F80CE1D04561D2B0C235603" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="21">Trochila ilicina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in ecological strategy (fungicolous symbiont); sizes of asci (102.4-111.2 
<normalizedToken id="CC7DBDC1F794B7A7BB1539EEA1F84880" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
10.5-11.6 
<normalizedToken id="7A74A750DBEFC321BD10B724CB60C33E" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
), ascospores (9.0-9.7 
<normalizedToken id="5CAF6928966756620E6BCEE2444B98C9" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
6.3-7.1 
<normalizedToken id="320B6969E487863FB53316B805B58FFF" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
), paraphyses (3.2-3.6 
<normalizedToken id="352F09DC1BB86A2916C0BB081DC81A66" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
wide); and the inamyloidity of its ascus apex.
</paragraph>
<caption id="67705C5228E9752F117216F69EFD53F4" doi="10.3897/mycokeys..62046.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/507853" pageId="0" pageNumber="21" start="Figure 4" startId="F4">
<paragraph id="1F5F7F9FC27F6E090E7CB05C6A3CE660" pageId="0" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis id="A62E78A227012BB738F934AD7130C8CA" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="21">Figure 4.</emphasis>
